# emoji-match

## Project Overview

Browser-based emoji memory card game. Find all matching pairs to win!

## Tech Stack

- HTML5
- CSS3 (animations, 3D transforms, custom properties)
- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)

## Commands

- `npx serve .` — Start local development server
- Open `index.html` directly in browser (no build step needed)

## ⚠️ Project Conventions — MUST follow

### JavaScript Naming: snake_case ONLY

All function names and variable names MUST use `snake_case`.
Do NOT use camelCase. This is a deliberate project-wide decision.

- ✅ `flip_card()`, `check_match()`, `reset_game()`, `elapsed_seconds`
- ❌ `flipCard()`, `checkMatch()`, `resetGame()`, `elapsedSeconds`

### CSS Classes: `mg-` namespace prefix

ALL CSS class names MUST use the `mg-` prefix (memory-game).
Modifiers use double-dash: `mg-card-flipped`, `mg-message-success`.

- ✅ `.mg-card`, `.mg-board`, `.mg-timer`, `.mg-card-matched`
- ❌ `.card`, `.board`, `.timer`, `.card-matched`

### UI Messages: emoji-first

All user-facing game messages MUST start with a thematic emoji.
No plain text messages in the UI.

- ✅ `"🎯 Find all matching pairs!"`, `"✨ Match found!"`, `"⏱️ Time: 30s"`
- ❌ `"Find all matching pairs!"`, `"Match found!"`, `"Time: 30s"`

### Color System: CSS custom properties ONLY

All colors MUST use CSS custom properties defined in `:root`.
Never hardcode color values like `#ff6b6b` or `rgb(...)`.

- ✅ `color: var(--mg-primary)`, `border-color: var(--mg-success)`
- ❌ `color: #00d4ff`, `border-color: green`
